     <h1>The 2007 Windfall Report</h1>

     <div class="byline-wrap">
       
         <span class="byline">by 
           Peter Newcomb
         </span>
         <img src="http://assets.portfolio.com/images/site/gfx/accent-dotted-pipe.gif" class="pipe" alt=""/>
       
       <span class="dateStamp">Mar 05 2008</span>
     </div><!-- /#byline_wrapper -->
                    
     
      <div id="headDeck" class="deck"><em>Vanity Fair</em> weighs in on America's 50 richest paydays: Who, what, and how much.</div>
     

    </div><!-- /#articleHead -->

    <div class="span-16 last">
       <!--[if !IE]>inner-rail<![endif]-->  
    <div class="inner-rail">
     <div class="top-bot-rules">

     
      <div class="promo module">
       <h3>
         <a href="http://www.portfolio.com/interactive-features/2007/12/wall-street-values">
           
  <img border="0" class="mltIcn" src="http://assets.portfolio.com/images/site/icn/icon_if.gif" style="display: inline;"/>


           Wall Street Family Values
           
             <img border="0" title="Wall Street Family Values" alt="Wall Street Family Values" src="http://assets.portfolio.com/images/site/editorial/Flash/interactive-feature/2007/12/wall-st-50/wallst_med.jpg" width="168" />
           
         </a>
         
           <div class="playMe">
             <a class="readMore" href="http://www.portfolio.com/interactive-features/2007/12/wall-street-values">View Interactive Feature</a>
           </div>
         
       </h3>
       <div class="blurb bodyText">
         <em>Cond&eacute; Nast Portfolio</em> on the most and least philanthropic wealthy people on Wall Street. 
         
           <a href="/multimedia/">See All Video & Multimedia</a>
         
         
       </div>
      </div>
     
     
     

     </div> <!-- /rules -->
    </div><!-- /inner-rail -->
   <!--[if !IE]>inner-rail<![endif]-->

    

    
    <div>
      <div id="photo">
       <img src="http://assets.portfolio.com/images/site/editorial/News/2008/03/windfall.jpg" width="372" height="226" alt="Windfall" />
       
       <div class="byline">Image: Portfolio.com</div>
       <span style="clear:left;"></span>
      </div>  <!-- /#photo -->
    </div>  
    

    

     
    <div id="content" class="bodyText">
     <div id="page1" class="articlePage">

      
       <p><span class="dropCap">Y</span>ou won't find Oprah Winfrey on the list. Nor will you find the legion of hedge fund managers who routinely collect hundreds of millions in any given year. That's because they're all just getting paid to do their day jobs.</p>
      
       <p>This list, compiled by <a href="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2008/04/50paydays200804" target="_blank"><em>Vanity Fair</em></a>, ranks the winners from last year's monster transactions: Stock cash-outs, I.P.O.'s, sales of companies, real-estate deals&mdash;even inheritances.</p>
      
       <p>Here are the Top 5 of the 50 players (and one lucky canine) whose bottom lines got the biggest boost last year.</p>
      
       <h4>1.</h4>
      
       <p><a href="http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/26682">BILL GATES</a>: $2.8 billion</p>
      
       <p>The world's richest man downloaded $2.5 billion worth of Microsoft stock last year. Throw in a few hundred million dollars in dividend income and his impending retirement will be all the more comfortable.</p>
      
       <h4>2.</h4>
      
       <p><a href="http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/1239683">PETE PETERSON</a>: $1.9 billion</p>
      
       <p>Peterson cashed out big-time in the Blackstone I.P.O. He intends to give a substantial portion of the proceeds to charity.</p>
      
       <h4>3.</h4>
      
       <p><a href="http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/340833">CHANDLER FAMILY</a>: $1.7 billion</p>
      
       <p>Seven years after selling Times Mirror (publisher of the Los Angeles Times) to Tribune Co. for stock, the forlorn newspaper clan pushed for the sale of Tribune to investor Sam Zell - this time for cash.</p>
      
       <h4>4.</h4>
      
       <p><a href="http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/1361653">JAMES JANNARD</a>: $1.3 billion</p>
      
       <p>The secretive founder of sunglasses-manufacturer Oakley sold his company to Italy's Luxottica Group for an eye-popping $2.1 billion.</p>
      
       <h4>5.</h4>
      
       <p><a href="http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/1342757">JERRY PERENCHIO</a>: $1.3 billion</p>
      
       <p>In March, the TV veteran (he was partners with All in the Family producer Norman Lear) said adios to Univision, the nation's largest Spanish-language broadcaster, for $13.7 billion.</p>
      
       <h4><a href="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2008/04/50paydays200804" target="_blank">The full list of the 50 top windfalls is at VanityFair.com.</a></h4>
      
       <p>Also on Portfolio.com:</strong></p>
      
       <p><ul><li><strong><a target="_self" href="http://www.portfolio.com/executives/features/2007/12/17/Family-Philanthropic-Efforts">Wall Street Family Values</a>:Family foundations are on the rise. Who's giving-and who's missing?</strong></li> <li><strong><a target="_self" href="http://www.portfolio.com/executives/features/2007/12/17/Wall-Street-Values-Main">The Givers</a>: Cond&eacute; Nast Portfolio's look at the most&mdash;and least&mdash;philanthropic on Wall Street.</strong></li> <li><strong><a target="_self" href="http://www.portfolio.com/interactive-features/2007/12/wall-street-values">Wall Street Values</a>: Find out more about who's giving&mdash;and who's missing.</strong></li> <li><strong><a target="_self" href="http://www.portfolio.com/views/columns/2007/10/15/Charity-Makes-Wealth">Giving Makes You Rich</a>: New proof that it pays to be charitable.</strong></li> <li><strong><a target="_self" href="http://www.portfolio.com/interactive-features/2007/10/philanthropy-calculator">Pass It On</a>: With charity, you get what you give ... and more.</strong></li></ul></p>
      

      
       
        <hr>
        
          
          
        
       
      

